{
  "name": "threeBallComboRekiss",
  "description": "All-head-on three-ball chain: cue -> A -> B, B banks off the right rail and re-kisses the now-stationary A, which rolls to a second rest. Exercises queue ordering and the rest-ball re-entering the static snapshot.",
  "derivation": [
    "Cue (-0.6,0) at 2 m/s hits A(0,0): t = 0.6 - 2r = 0.54285; contact (-0.05715, 0); speed sqrt(4 - 0.54285) ~= 1.859341; cue stuns to rest.",
    "A departs at 0.96*1.859341 ~= 1.784968; hits B(0.4, 0) after t = 0.4 - 2r = 0.34285 at contact (0.34285, 0); speed there ~= 1.686197; A stuns to rest at (0.34285, 0).",
    "B departs at 0.96*1.686197 ~= 1.618749; reaches the right reflection line x = 1.241425 after 0.841425 m at ~1.333763 m/s; bounces back at 0.75x ~= 1.000322 m/s.",
    "B (moving -x) re-hits A: contact when B center is at 0.34285 + 2r = 0.4 (its own start point!), after 0.841425 m, at ~0.399023 m/s; B stuns to rest at (0.4, 0).",
    "A takes 0.96*0.399023 ~= 0.383062 m/s, rolls v^2/(2a) ~= 0.146736 m from (0.34285, 0) to rest at ~(0.196114, 0).",
    "(Numbers in the JSON are exact IEEE doubles; the commentary rounds to 6 dp.)"
  ],
